    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 9, 2025</p>

        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>CBeautyInsider ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when you use our Service.</p>
        <div class="highlight">
            <p><strong>By using CBeautyInsider, you agree to the collection and use of information as described in this policy.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        
        <h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Email address, name (if provided)</li>
            <li><strong>TikTok Account Data:</strong> TikTok username, profile information obtained through TikTok Login Kit</li>
            <li><strong>Content Data:</strong> Videos, scripts, captions, and metadata you create or upload</li>
            <li><strong>Settings and Preferences:</strong> Content scheduling preferences, API configurations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Features used, pages viewed, time spent on Service</li>
            <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Browser type, device information, IP address</li>
            <li><strong>Error Logs:</strong> Technical issues and crash reports for debugging</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.3 Third-Party Data</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>TikTok API Data:</strong> Information retrieved through TikTok's API when you authorize access</li>
            <li><strong>Dropbox Data:</strong> File storage information if you connect Dropbox</li>
            <li><strong>Claude AI:</strong> Content analyzed for script generation (not stored by Anthropic beyond processing)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        
        <h3>3.1 Provide and Improve Service</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Enable content posting to your TikTok account</li>
            <li>Generate AI-powered scripts</li>
            <li>Store and organize your content</li>
            <li>Schedule and manage posts</li>
            <li>Provide customer support</li>
            <li>Fix bugs and improve performance</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Communication</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Send service-related notifications</li>
            <li>Respond to inquiries and support requests</li>
            <li>Notify you of important updates or changes</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.3 Analytics and Research</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Understand how users interact with the Service</li>
            <li>Improve features and user experience</li>
            <li>Analyze usage patterns (aggregated and anonymized)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Share Your Information</h2>
        
        <h3>4.1 Third-Party Service Providers</h3>
        <p>We share data with third parties necessary to operate the Service:</p>

        <div class="service-box">
            <p><strong>TikTok</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>We send videos, captions, and metadata to post on your behalf</li>
                <li>Governed by TikTok's Privacy Policy</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="service-box">
            <p><strong>Dropbox</strong> (if connected)</p>
            <ul>
                <li>We store your content files in your Dropbox account</li>
                <li>Governed by Dropbox's Privacy Policy</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="service-box">
            <p><strong>Anthropic (Claude AI)</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>We send screenshots and text for script generation</li>
                <li>Data is not stored or trained on by Anthropic</li>
                <li>Governed by Anthropic's Privacy Policy</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="service-box">
            <p><strong>Cloud Infrastructure Providers</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>We use hosting services to store data and run the Service</li>
                <li>All providers are GDPR/CCPA compliant</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h3>4.2 Legal Requirements</h3>
        <p>We may disclose information if required by law or to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Comply with legal processes or government requests</li>
            <li>Enforce our Terms of Service</li>
            <li>Protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property</li>
            <li>Prevent fraud or security issues</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.3 Business Transfers</h3>
        <p>If CBeautyInsider is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale, your information may be transferred. We will notify you before your data is transferred and subject to a different privacy policy.</p>

        <div class="highlight">
            <h3>4.4 What We Don't Do</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>We do NOT sell your personal information to third parties</li>
                <li>We do NOT share your content publicly without your permission</li>
                <li>We do NOT use your content to train AI models without consent</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
        
        <h3>5.1 Where We Store Data</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>User Data:</strong> Stored on secure cloud servers (United States)</li>
            <li><strong>Content Files:</strong> Stored in your connected cloud storage (Dropbox)</li>
            <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> Some data stored locally in your browser</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.2 Security Measures</h3>
        <p>We implement industry-standard security measures:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Encryption in transit (HTTPS/TLS)</li>
            <li>Encryption at rest for sensitive data</li>
            <li>Secure API authentication (OAuth 2.0)</li>
            <li>Regular security audits</li>
            <li>Access controls and monitoring</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.3 Data Retention</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Active Accounts:</strong> Data retained while your account is active</li>
            <li><strong>Deleted Accounts:</strong> Data deleted within 30 days of account deletion</li>
            <li><strong>Backup Data:</strong> May be retained for up to 90 days in backups</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> Some data retained longer if required by law</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        
        <h3>6.1 Access and Control</h3>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Update or correct inaccurate information</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your account and data</li>
            <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Export your data in a standard format</li>
            <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to certain data processing activities</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6.2 TikTok Authorization</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>You can revoke TikTok access at any time through TikTok's settings</li>
            <li>Revoking access will disable posting features but preserve your other data</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6.3 Communication Preferences</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>You can opt out of non-essential emails</li>
            <li>Service-related notifications cannot be disabled while using the Service</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="warning">
            <h3>6.4 How to Exercise Your Rights</h3>
            <p><strong>Contact us at:</strong> cbeautyinsider@gmail.com</p>
            <p>We will respond within 30 days of verified requests.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        
        <h3>7.1 Cookies We Use</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for Service functionality (authentication, session management)</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand usage patterns</li>
            <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> Remember your settings</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Your Cookie Choices</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Most browsers allow you to control cookies through settings</li>
            <li>Blocking essential cookies may prevent Service functionality</li>
            <li>Third-party cookies are governed by third-party privacy policies</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
        <p>The Service may contain links to third-party websites or integrate with third-party services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.</p>

        <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>CBeautyInsider is not intended for users under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect information from children. If you believe we have collected information from a child, contact us immediately, and we will delete it.</p>

        <h2>10. International Users</h2>
        
        <h3>10.1 Data Transfers</h3>
        <p>If you access the Service from outside the United States, your data may be transferred to and processed in the United States.</p>

        <h3>10.2 EU/UK Users (GDPR)</h3>
        <p>If you are in the EU or UK, you have additional rights under GDPR:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Right to restrict processing</li>
            <li>Right to data portability</li>
            <li>Right to object to automated decision-making</li>
            <li>Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>10.3 California Users (CCPA)</h3>
        <p>If you are a California resident, you have rights under CCPA:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Right to know what personal information is collected</li>
            <li>Right to delete personal information</li>
            <li>Right to opt-out of sale (we do not sell personal information)</li>
            <li>Right to non-discrimination for exercising your rights</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. AI-Generated Content</h2>
        
        <h3>11.1 Script Generation</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Screenshots and text are sent to Claude AI (Anthropic) for script generation</li>
            <li>Anthropic does not store or train on your data</li>
            <li>Generated scripts are suggestions and may contain errors</li>
            <li>You are responsible for reviewing all AI-generated content</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>11.2 Content Responsibility</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>We do not guarantee accuracy of AI-generated content</li>
            <li>You must review and approve all content before posting</li>
            <li>We are not liable for issues arising from AI-generated content</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted with an updated "Last Updated" date. Significant changes will be notified via:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Email notification</li>
            <li>In-app notification</li>
            <li>Prominent notice on our website</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.</p>

